Fouad Zakariyya (or Fud Zakary) (b. 1927 Port Said - d. March 2010) was an Egyptian philosopher, and critic of Islamist thought who is known as the father of Arab existentialism. He was a recipient of the Sultan Bin Ali Al Owais Cultural Award for Humanities and Future Studies.[1] He earned his doctorate in philosophy at Cairo's Ain Shams University in 1956 and taught at Kuwait University for many years.[2]
